t! The advantage of this approach is extremely robust, and keeps the UI responsive!\n\nI\'m also working on `CollectorProfile` and other data structures. We will use a `gemini-3.5-flash` model to write highly detailed Indonesian summaries! I\'m now setting up the express server with a POST/api/analyze endpoint that will receive customer records, activity data, collector profiles, and trigger the engine.\n\n\n**Confirming Vite Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating Vite and confirming its behavior in development and production, so I can ensure it correctly serves the application and static assets. I\'m double-checking the Haversine distance calculation to ensure accuracy in our calculations, since this is critical to the collector\'s approach. I\'m also ensuring the dashboard components are correct.\n\n\n**Calculating Recency Weights**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the recency weighting logic, calculating the haversine distance. I\'ve been considering how to determine the reference date for recency calculations and have decided to automatically detect the latest activity timestamp in the dataset to provide correct weights for activities.\n\n\n"
