  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Building the Server**\n\nOkay, great! I have the mock datasets ready. I\'m now focused on building a robust `server.ts` file to serve as the Express full-stack backend. I\'m taking a moment to understand the structure of a full-stack `server.ts` file incorporating Vite middleware, though.\n\n\n**Constructing the API**\n\nI\'m now integrating the Gemini API within the `/api/analyze` route. The goal is to set up a deterministic analysis pipeline. I\'m focusing on ensuring it handles requests correctly. I\'ll need to define the request structure for input data and determine how to format the responses.\n\n\n**Designing the Prompt**\n\nI\'m now designing the system prompt for Gemini! I\'ll feed the model customer info and collector metrics. The prompt will request rewritten Indonesian `executive_summary`, `risk_analysis`, and `recommended_actions`. I need to structure this prompt carefully, considering input format and desired output style for optimal results. It\'s becoming pretty exciting!\n\n\n**Defining JSON Output**\n\nI\'ve specified the desired JSON output format in Bahasa Indonesia: `executive_summary`, `risk_analysis`, and `recommended_actions`. I need to ensure the Gemini API will generate this *exact* JSON structure. I\'ve also detailed precise instructions for the content of each field, emphasizing formal, data-driven language and practical recommendations.\n\nI\'m now thinking about robustness: If the Gemini API fails, I\'ll fallback to a rule-based system, a bulletproof approach. I\'ll need to handle potential errors like missing API keys or rate limits seamlessly.\n\n\n**Refining the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'m verifying the import of the analysis engine within `server.ts`. It seems straightforward: a relative import handles it. I\'m double-checking the POST request\'s input parameters for the `/api/analyze` route to ensure correct parsing of the customer and profile data. I\'m confirming that the structure aligns with what\'s expected for analysis.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/server.ts` to implement the full-stack backend server. It serves:\n1. The static React files (or compiles on the fly via Vite in dev mode).\n2. The headless automated `POST /api/analyze` REST endpoint. This accepts Customer, Collector Profile list, and Activity history. It performs deep calculations using the same TypeScript analysis engine, and optionally enhances the Indonesian Executive Summary and Risks through the Gemini `gemini-3.5-flash` model when `GEMINI_API_KEY` is present, with seamless rule-based Indonesian summaries as a reliable local fallback."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 149161899
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
