  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Building UI Components**\n\nOkay, the stylesheet is updated and I\'ve shifted focus to UI components. Currently, I\'m sketching out the needed components. First up, I\'m building a custom interactive map component at `/src/components/InteractiveMap.tsx`. It will utilize an HTML5 SVG map to allow user interactions.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Map\'s Elements**\n\nNow, I\'m delving into the visual aspects of the map. I\'ve decided on an SVG-based approach for an interactive map visualization, rejecting external JS map engines for the reasons mentioned before. I\'m focusing on key elements: a pulse anchor for the customer\'s coordinate, radius circles (1km emerald, 1-3km amber) with labels, and color-coded activity locations, and connecting lines. This design provides a clear, offline-compatible visual representation.\n\n\n**Designing Dynamic Scaling**\n\nI\'m now focused on dynamic scaling for the interactive map component. The goal is a high-craftsmanship UI. I\'m writing `/src/components/InteractiveMap.tsx` and now need to ensure the map dynamically scales activities to fit the viewport. I\'m calculating bounds from latitude/longitude coordinates to fit the SVG box. The customer coordinate will be the center, and a 3.5 km circle should fit perfectly.\n\n\n**Calculating Coordinate Mappings**\n\nI\'ve nailed down the coordinate mapping logic for the interactive map. The math ensures the customer is perfectly centered, and radius circles maintain accurate proportions.  I\'ve derived the equations for `dLat` and `dLng` based on a `zoomRad` value to fit the map within the SVG boundaries, ensuring circular representations.  This provides a solid foundation for dynamic scaling and precise visual representation. I\'ve now defined the SVG radius calculation to display distances accurately.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/InteractiveMap.tsx` to handle visual rendering of the territory coordinates. It uses a custom SVG engine that dynamically maps GPS coordinates to SVG canvas space, centers the customer, draws exact concentric 1km and 3km translucent circles, and overlays interactive, hovered collector activity pins colored by collector. This ensures a responsive, lag-free map experience in the sandbox environment."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 971532783
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
