  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Assessing Project Completion**\n\nI\'m evaluating the remaining components for this project. We\'ve got `CollectorCard.tsx`, and I\'m cross-referencing that with `DataImporter.tsx`, `InteractiveMap.tsx`, and `JSONOutput.tsx` to get a good picture of completion. It looks like we still have a bit more to go, so now I\'m listing what is still left.\n\n\n**Designing App Integration**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `/src/App.tsx`, the crucial integration point. The core design includes two analysis pathways: a real-time, client-side approach using `runAnalysis` directly for immediate updates during variable edits, and a server-side fetch from `/api/analyze` for a Gemini AI-powered report summary accessible through a toggle or button. The initial UI layout will include a header block with the custom title \"Collection Territory Intelligence System.\"\n\n\n**Defining Dashboard Layout**\n\nI\'m solidifying the dashboard\'s bento grid. I\'m focusing on the responsive column layout using Tailwind, specifically the three core panels: the input panel (left), the interactive map and collector list (middle), and the executive summary/JSON output panel (right). The goal is a clean, user-friendly presentation across different screen sizes. I\'m also confirming the panel component mapping now.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/App.tsx` to serve as the unified cockpit for our dashboard. It integrates matching react hook states for custom data streams (including customers, profiles, and activity streams). It runs the mathematical scoring engine directly on the client side for subsecond latency, and offers a tactical \"Tingkatkan dengan Gemini AI\" button which hits the Express backend `/api/analyze` to produce customized Indonesian executive analysis cards when `GEMINI_API_KEY` is present. It layouts everything into a 3-column responsive bento dashboard."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 517813379
    }
